# Autux Environment Change Log

This document details every change Autux makes to your Termux and Android environment, for transparency and control.

---

## System & Environment Variables
- Sets and exports key environment variables:
  - `VENV`, `LX`, `PX`, `FPy`, `FBash`, `CACHE`, `SETTINGS`, `SETTINGS_HASH_FILE`, and more.
- Adds Autux Python and Bash script directories to your `PATH` for global access.

## File System & Directories
- Creates and manages:
  - `$HOME/.local/bin` (for user scripts)
  - `$VENV/scripts` (for Python venv scripts)
  - `$HOME/.cache/autux` (for cache/state)
  - `$HOME/.local/share/autux/settings` (for settings)
- Copies all scripts from `FPy` and `FBash` to `PX` and `LX`.
- Sets executable permissions on all scripts in `PX` and `LX`.

## Shell & Session
- Appends Autux configuration comments and sourcing to `bash.bashrc`.
- Clears or resets shell history files:
  - Removes `$HOME/.lesshst` if present.
  - Clears `$HOME/.bash_history`.
- Optionally sets a custom Message of the Day (MOTD) in `$PREFIX/etc/motd`.

## ADB & Device
- Automates ADB over TCP/IP setup (port 5555), including:
  - Setting `service.adb.tcp.port` property.
  - Restarting `adbd` service for wireless debugging.
- Attempts to connect to all IPs listed in settings for ADB.
- Provides interactive setup for USB debugging and ADB connection.

## Package Management
- Updates all `pkg` and `apt` packages during setup.
- Installs required Termux and Python dependencies (see `reqs/`).
- Optionally enables extra repositories (e.g., x11-repo).

## Settings & Aliases
- Reads and applies settings from `src/configs/settings.jsonc`:
  - App aliases for quick launching.
  - Shell alias settings (e.g., `ls -a`).
  - Custom command associations.
- Monitors settings file for changes and reapplies if modified.

## Storage & Permissions
- Ensures Termux has storage permissions and access to shared storage.
- Creates documentation and local bin directories as needed.

## Python Virtual Environment
- Sets up and activates a Python venv in `$VENV`.
- Installs Python dependencies from `reqs/PIP_Req.txt`.

## Other
- Provides interactive prompts for user input during setup and configuration.
- Maintains a cache/state file to avoid repeating completed setup steps.

---

**Note:** All changes are designed to be idempotent and safe for repeated runs. For full details, see the setup and session scripts in `src/bin/`.
